h3001.definition: a primitive root; to be ashamed, confused or disappointed; also (as failing) to dry up (as water) or wither (as herbage); be ashamed, clean, be confounded, (make) dry (up), (do) shame(-fully), × utterly, wither (away).

h3003.definition: the same as {{h3002}} (also יָבֵישׁ; often with the addition of {{h1568}}, i.e. Jabesh of Gilad); Jobesh, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine; Jobesh (-Gilead).

h3005.definition: from the same as {{h1314}}; fragrant; Jibsam, an Israelite; Jibsam.

h3006.definition: a variation of {{h3004}}; dry ground; dry land.

h3008.definition: from {{h1350}}; avenger; Jigal, the name of three Israelites; Igal, Igeal.

h3009.definition: a primitive root; to dig or plow; husbandman.

h3011.definition: feminine from {{h1361}}; hillock; Jogbehah, a place East of the Jordan; Jogbehah.

h3012.definition: from {{h1431}} and {{h3050}}; magnified of Jah; Jigdaljah, an Israelite; Igdaliah.

h3013.definition: a primitive root; to grieve; afflict, cause grief, grieve, sorrowful, vex.

h3014.definition: a primitive root (probably rather the same as {{h3013}} through the common idea of dissatisfaction); to push away; be removed.

h3017.definition: probably from {{h1481}}; a lodging; Jagur, a place in Palestine; Jagur.

h3018.definition: from {{h3021}}; toil; hence, a work, produce, property (as the result of labor); labour, work.

h3020.definition: from {{h1540}}; exiled; Jogli, an Israelite; Jogli.

h3021.definition: a primitive root; properly, to gasp; hence, to be exhausted, to tire, to toil; faint, (make to) labour, (be) weary.

h3022.definition: from {{h3021}}; earnings (as the product of toil); that which he laboured for.

h3023.definition: from {{h3021}}; tired; hence (transitive) tiresome; full of labour, weary.

h3025.definition: a primitive root; to fear; be afraid, fear.

h3026.definition: (Aramaic) from a word derived from an unused root (meaning to gather) and a derivation of a root corresponding to {{h7717}}; heap of the testimony; Jegar-Sahadutha, a cairn East of the Jordan; Jegar-Sahadutha.

h3027.definition: a primitive word; a hand (the open one [indicating power, means, direction, etc.], in distinction from {{h3709}}, the closed one); used (as noun, adverb, etc.) in a great variety of applications, both literally and figuratively, both proximate and remote [as follows]; (  be) able, × about,   armholes, at, axletree, because of, beside, border, × bounty,   broad, (broken-) handed, × by, charge, coast,   consecrate,   creditor, custody, debt, dominion, × enough,   fellowship, force, × from, hand(-staves, -y work), × he, himself, × in, labour,   large, ledge, (left-) handed, means, × mine, ministry, near, × of, × order, ordinance, × our, parts, pain, power, × presumptuously, service, side, sore, state, stay, draw with strength, stroke,   swear, terror, × thee, × by them, × themselves, × thine own, × thou, through, × throwing,   thumb, times, × to, × under, × us, × wait on, (way-) side, where,   wide, × with (him, me, you), work,   yield, × yourselves.

h3030.definition: of uncertain derivation; Jidalah, a place in Palestine; Idalah.

h3031.definition: from the same as {{h1706}}; perhaps honeyed; Jidbash, an Israelite; Idbash.

h3032.definition: a primitive root; (compare {{h3034}}); properly, to handle, i.e. to throw, e.g. lots; cast.

h3033.definition: from {{h3039}}; properly, affection; concretely, a darling object; dearly beloved.

h3034.definition: a primitive root; used only as denominative from {{h3027}}; literally, to use (i.e. hold out) the hand; physically, to throw (a stone, an arrow) at or away; especially to revere or worship (with extended hands); intensively, to bemoan (by wringing the hands); cast (out), (make) confess(-ion), praise, shoot, (give) thank(-ful, -s, -sgiving).

h3035.definition: from {{h3034}}; praised; Jiddo, an Israelite; Iddo.

h3036.definition: from {{h3034}}; thankful; Jadon, an Israelite; Jadon.

h3037.definition: from {{h3045}}; knowing; Jaddua, the name of two Israelites; Jaddua.

h3038.definition: or יְדֻתוּן; or יְדִיתוּן; probably from {{h3034}}; laudatory; Jeduthun, an Israelite; Jeduthun.

h3039.definition: from the same as {{h1730}}; loved; amiable, (well-) beloved, loves.

h3040.definition: feminine of {{h3039}}; beloved; Jedidah, an Israelitess; Jedidah.

h3041.definition: from {{h3039}} and {{h3050}}; beloved of Jah; Jedidejah, a name of Solomon; Jedidiah.

h3042.definition: from {{h3034}} and {{h3050}}; praised of Jah; Jedajah, the name of two Israelites; Jedaiah.

h3043.definition: from {{h3045}} and {{h410}}; knowing God; Jediael, the name of three Israelites; Jediael.

h3044.definition: from {{h1811}}; tearful; Jidlaph, a Mesopotamian; Jidlaph.

h3045.definition: a primitive root; to know (properly, to ascertain by seeing); used in a great variety of senses, figuratively, literally, euphemistically and inferentially (including observation, care, recognition; and causatively, instruction, designation, punishment, etc.); acknowledge, acquaintance(-ted with), advise, answer, appoint, assuredly, be aware, (un-) awares, can(-not), certainly, comprehend, consider, × could they, cunning, declare, be diligent, (can, cause to) discern, discover, endued with, familiar friend, famous, feel, can have, be (ig-) norant, instruct, kinsfolk, kinsman, (cause to let, make) know, (come to give, have, take) knowledge, have (knowledge), (be, make, make to be, make self) known,   be learned,   lie by man, mark, perceive, privy to, × prognosticator, regard, have respect, skilful, shew, can (man of) skill, be sure, of a surety, teach, (can) tell, understand, have (understanding), × will be, wist, wit, wot.

h3046.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3045}}; certify, know, make known, teach.

h3047.definition: from {{h3045}}; knowing; Jada, an Israelite; Jada.

h3048.definition: from {{h3045}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has known; Jedajah, the name of two Israelites; Jedaiah.

h3049.definition: from {{h3045}}; properly, a knowing one; specifically, a conjurer; (by impl) a ghost; wizard.

h3050.definition: contraction for {{h3068}}, and meaning the same; Jah, the sacred name; Jah, the Lord, most vehement. Compare names in '-iah,' '-jah.'

h3051.definition: a primitive root; to give (whether literal or figurative); generally, to put; imperatively (reflexive) come; ascribe, bring, come on, give, go, set, take.

h3052.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3051}}; deliver, give, lay,   prolong, pay, yield.

h3053.definition: from {{h3051}}; properly, what is given (by Providence), i.e. a lot; burden.

h3054.definition: denominative from a form corresponding to {{h3061}}; to Judaize, i.e. become Jewish; become Jews.

h3055.definition: a briefer form of one corresponding to {{h3061}}; Jehud, a place in Palestine; Jehud.

h3056.definition: perhaps from a form corresponding to {{h3061}}; Judaistic; Jehdai, an Israelite; Jehdai.

h3057.definition: feminine of {{h3064}}; Jehudijah, a Jewess; Jehudijah.

h3058.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h1931}}; Jehovah (is) He; Jehu, the name of five Israelites; Jehu.

h3059.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h270}}; Jehovah-seized; Jehoachaz, the name of three Israelites; Jehoahaz. Compare {{h3099}}.

h3060.definition: from {{h3068}} and (perhaps) {{h784}}; Jehovah-fired; Jehoash, the name of two Israelite kings; Jehoash. Compare {{h3101}}.

h3061.definition: (Aramaic) contracted from a form corresponding to {{h3063}}; properly, Judah, hence, Judaea; Jewry, Judah, Judea.

h3062.definition: (Aramaic) patrial from {{h3061}}; a Jehudaite (or Judaite), i.e. Jew; Jew.

h3063.definition: from {{h3034}}; celebrated; Jehudah (or Judah), the name of five Israelites; also of the tribe descended from the first, and of its territory; Judah.

h3064.definition: patronymically from {{h3063}}; a Jehudite (i.e. Judaite or Jew), or descendant of Jehudah (i.e. Judah); Jew.

h3065.definition: the same as {{h3064}}; Jehudi, an Israelite; Jehudi.

h3066.definition: feminine of {{h3064}}; the Jewish (used adverbially) language; in the Jews' language.

h3067.definition: the same as {{h3066}}; Jewess; Jehudith, a Canaanitess; Judith.

h3068.definition: from {{h1961}}; (the) self-Existent or Eternal; Jeho-vah, Jewish national name of God; Jehovah, the Lord. Compare {{h3050}}, {{h3069}}.

h3069.definition: a variation of {{h3068}} [used after {{h136}}, and pronounced by Jews as {{h430}}, in order to prevent the repetition of the same sound, since they elsewhere pronounce {{h3068}} as {{h136}}]; God.

h3070.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h7200}}; Jehovah will see (to it); Jehovah-Jireh, a symbolical name for Mount Moriah; Jehovah-jireh.

h3071.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h5251}} with the prononimal suffix; Jehovah (is) my banner; Jehovah-Nissi, a symbolical name of an altar in the Desert; Jehovah-nissi.

h3072.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h6664}} with pronominal suffix; Jehovah (is) our right; Jehovah-Tsidkenu, a symbolical epithet of the Messiah and of Jerusalem; the Lord our righteousness.

h3073.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h7965}}; Jehovah (is) peace; Jehovah-Shalom, a symbolical name of an altar in Palestine; Jehovah-shalom.

h3074.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h8033}} with directive enclitic; Jehovah (is) thither; Jehovah-Shammah, a symbolic title of Jerusalem; Jehovahshammah.

h3075.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h2064}}; Jehovah-endowed; Jehozabad, the name of three Israelites; Jehozabad. Compare {{h3107}}.

h3076.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h2603}}; Jehovah-favored; Jehochanan, the name of eight Israelites; Jehohanan, Johanan. Compare {{h3110}}.

h3077.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h3045}}; Jehovah-known; Jehojada, the name of three Israelites; Jehoiada. Compare {{h3111}}.

h3078.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h3559}}; Jehovah will establish; Jehojakin, a Jewish king; Jehoiachin. Compare {{h3112}}.

h3079.definition: from {{h3068}} abbreviated and {{h6965}}; Jehovah will raise; Jehojakim, a Jewish king; Jehoiakim. Compare {{h3113}}.

h3080.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h7378}}; Jehovah will contend; Jehojarib, the name of two Israelites; Jehoiarib. Compare {{h3114}}.

h3081.definition: from {{h3201}}; potent; Jehukal, an Israelite; Jehucal. Compare {{h3116}}.

h3082.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h5068}}; Jehovah-largessed; Jehonadab, the name of an Israelite and of an Arab; Jehonadab, Jonadab. Compare {{h3122}}.

h3083.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h5414}}; Jehovah-given; Jehonathan, the name of four Israelites; Jonathan. Compare {{h3129}}.

h3084.definition: a fuller form of {{h3130}}; Jehoseph (i.e. Joseph), a son of Jacob; Joseph.

h3085.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h5710}}; Jehovah-adorned; Jehoaddah, an Israelite; Jehoada.

h3086.definition: or יְהוֹעַדָּן; from {{h3068}} and {{h5727}}; Jehovahpleased; Jehoaddin or Jehoaddan, an Israelitess; Jehoaddan.

h3087.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h6663}}; Jehovah-righted; Jehotsadak, an Israelite; Jehozadek, Josedech. Compare {{h3136}}.

h3088.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h7311}}; Jehovah-raised; Jehoram, the name of a Syrian and of three Israelites; Jehoram, Joram. Compare {{h3141}}.

h3089.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h7650}}; Jehovah-sworn; Jehosheba, an Israelitess; Jehosheba. Compare {{h3090}}.

h3090.definition: a form of {{h3089}}; Jehoshabath, an Israelitess; Jehoshabeath.

h3091.definition: or יְהוֹשֻׁעַ; from {{h3068}} and {{h3467}}; Jehovah-saved; Jehoshua (i.e. Joshua), the Jewish leader; Jehoshua, Jehoshuah, Joshua. Compare {{h1954}}, {{h3442}}.

h3092.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h8199}}; Jehovah-judged; Jehoshaphat, the name of six Israelites; also of a valley near Jerusalem; Jehoshaphat. Compare {{h3146}}.

h3093.definition: probably from the same as {{h2022}}; elated; hence, arrogant; haughty, proud.

h3094.definition: from {{h1984}} and {{h410}}; praising God; Jehallelel, the name of two Israelites; Jehalellel, Jehalelel.

h3095.definition: from {{h1986}} (in the sense of hardness); a precious stone, probably onyx; diamond.

h3096.definition: or יַהְצָה; or (feminine) יַהְצָה; from an unused root meaning to stamp; perhaps threshing-floor; Jahats or Jahtsah, a place East of the Jordan; Jahaz, Jahazah, Jahzah.

h3097.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h1}}; Jehovah-fathered; Joab, the name of three Israelites; Joab.

h3098.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h251}}; Jehovah-brothered; Joach, the name of four Israelites; Joah.

h3099.definition: a form of {{h3059}}; Joachaz, the name of two Israelites; Jehoahaz, Joahaz.

h3100.definition: from {{h3068}} and {{h410}}; Jehovah (is his) God; Joel, the name of twelve Israelites; Joel.
